TITLE: Severed head, hands found in freezer of recently-sold Colorado home
SUMMARY: Human remains were found in a freezer at a recently-sold home in Grand Junction, Colorado, the Mesa County Sheriff's Office reported Thursday.

TITLE: Atlanta Opera to stage COVID-updated version of Puccini classic
SUMMARY: The Atlanta Opera will stage Puccini's "La Bohéme," updated for the COVID-19 pandemic, as a part of its 45th anniversary season later this year.

TITLE: Namibian president to undergo cancer treatment
SUMMARY: Namibian President Hage Geingob will be treated for cancer after routine examinations led to its detection. No further details on the 82-year-old's condition were reported.

TITLE: Alec Baldwin faces new indictment in 'Rust' movie set shooting
SUMMARY: Alec Baldwin faces a new charge of involuntary manslaughter nearly a year after initial charges were dropped in connection with the accidental shooting of Halyna Hutchins.

TITLE: Bill Belichick 'top candidate' for Falcons head coaching job with 'more meetings to come': report
SUMMARY: Bill Belichick is reportedly the 'top candidate' for the Atlanta Falcons head coach opening, and he will conduct a second interview on Friday.

TITLE: Missing New Hampshire hiker's body recovered from White Mountains after he was stranded in cold
SUMMARY: Rescue teams in New Hampshire recovered the body of a outdoorsman who was killed by severe weather conditions while hiking in the state's White Mountains.

TITLE: New York kitty is up for adoption after he was rescued from hoarding home on Thanksgiving holiday
SUMMARY: A cat from New York is looking for his forever home after being rescued from a hoarding house on Thanksgiving. Meet Thyme — the sun-basking cat who loves others.

TITLE: Trump, GOP skeptics of Ukraine aid balk at potential McConnell-Schumer border deal
SUMMARY: Former President Trump insists Republicans reject any border security deal lacking comprehensive measures to halt illegal migration.

TITLE: Japan becomes the fifth country to reach the moon after its spacecraft landed on the lunar surface
SUMMARY: The unmanned Japanese spacecraft SLIM landed on the moon this weekend, marking a first for the East Asian nation, but problems with its solar panels appear to imperil the mission.

TITLE: Bloomberg reporter says he was ‘physically shoved’ by staffer for Chicago Mayor Brandon Johnson
SUMMARY: Bloomberg reporter Ian Kullgren said he was “physically shoved" by a staffer for Chicago Mayor Brandon Johnson when attempting to ask a question on Friday.

TITLE: Biden admin failing to track Chinese ownership of US farmland: govt watchdog
SUMMARY: The Department of Agriculture is failing to properly track foreign investment in agricultural land, leaving the nation's food security vulnerable, a watchdog agency found.

TITLE: Maine lawmaker warns residents alarmed by transgender youth bill that strips parents' rights: 'Huge outcry'
SUMMARY: A Republican lawmaker criticized Democrats pushing a transgender safe haven bill for teenagers that wouldn't require parental consent to treat out-of-state minors.

TITLE: Champion bodybuilder Chad McCrary dead at 49, brother confirms: 'Just an all-around good man'
SUMMARY: A 2005 motocross accident left Chad McCrary paralyzed from the waist down, but the champion bodybuilder did not let the traumatic event keep him from competition.

TITLE: Barbara Lee claims White man at Capitol tried to block her from entering elevator, accused her of theft
SUMMARY: Rep. Barbara Lee, D-Calif., claims she encountered "personal racism" when a White man blocked her from entering the members-only elevator in the Capitol Building.

TITLE: Prince Harry withdraws lawsuit against UK publisher the day he was due to provide defense of claims
SUMMARY: Prince Harry dropped his lawsuit against the Daily Mail the day he was due to provide the judge documents to support his argument that he'd been defamed.

TITLE: Washington, D.C., firefighters jump into action as explosion destroys convenience store: video
SUMMARY: A video has captured the moment firefighters reacted to an explosion that ripped through a building in Washington, D.C.’s Anacostia neighborhood.

TITLE: Hawley demands answers from TSA on migrants using controversial app to board planes: ‘This is outrageous’
SUMMARY: Sen. Josh Hawley is seeking answers from the Biden administration over an initiative to verify documentation for migrants seeking to fly using CBP One.

TITLE: EU chief says Israel was responsible for Hamas' surge to power in Gaza: 'Financed by the government'
SUMMARY: During a speech in Spain, the European Union’s foreign policy chief Josep Borrell said Israel was responsible for financing Hamas and their surge to power in Gaza.

TITLE: Tim Scott to endorse Trump at rally in New Hampshire Friday evening
SUMMARY: Sen. Tim Scott of South Carolina is endorsing former President Donald Trump in the 2024 Republican nomination race, Fox News confirmed on Friday.

TITLE: Jack Burke Jr, 2-time major champion golfer who was the oldest living Masters winner, dead at 100
SUMMARY: Jack Burke Jr., a World Golf Hall of Famer and two-time major champion, has died at the age of 100. He was a Masters champion who shared a locker with Tiger Woods.

TITLE: Biden's Iran nuclear containment policy failing as UN warns regime has enough material for 'several' warheads
SUMMARY: The International Atomic Energy Agency chief Rafael Grossi has repeatedly complained about Iran's lack of transparency over the past year and the difficulty trying to obtain compliance.

TITLE: Snoop Dogg turned down OnlyFans despite claims he could have made $100M
SUMMARY: Snoop Dogg claims he was told he could make $100 million on OnlyFans, but he stayed away from the adult content platform due to his wife. The rapper married Shante Broadus in 1997.

TITLE: RFK Jr catches waves with surfing legend Kelly Slater for birthday while campaigning in Hawaii
SUMMARY: Independent presidential candidate Robert F. Kennedy Jr., caught waves with surfing legend Kelly Slater in Hawaii for his birthday, posting the video to X.

TITLE: Pro-Palestinian students demand Israeli prime minister's name be removed from campus library
SUMMARY: Student protesters at the University of Wisconsin-Milwaukee are petitioning to change the name of the Golda Meir Library, named after the former prime minister of Israel.

TITLE: 'Laughing' suspect in LSU student attack indicted on video recording
SUMMARY: One of the suspects connected to the alleged rape of LSU sophomore Madison Brooks, who allegedly videotaped the incident, is facing more charges
